DESCRIPTION:Join us on Tuesday\, July 14th from 4-8 PM at Whispering Vine Fourth Street for an evening of Oakville wines from Groth paired with a flatbread included with the tasting. Before Oakville became an appellation\, Groth's estate vineyard grew from a family dream\, neighborhood friendship\, and a leap of faith. Today\, Ted Henry continues Groth's vine-to-bottle focus as Head Winemaker and Director of Winegrowing while bringing new precision to farming and winemaking.\nTasting Fee: $45 (includes tasting and flatbread)\nWith Special Guest:\nTed Henry\, Head Winemaker and Director of Winegrowing\nReserve your Spot: https://www.exploretock.com/whisperingvine4thstreet/experience/540467/flights-flatbread-tasting-groth\nFeatured Wines:\n- Groth Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 - Oakville estate Cabernet with black cherry\, loamy earth\, plush new-oak texture\, and a long\, velvety finish.\n- Groth Oakcross 2020 - Polished and velvety\, with deep blackberry and blueberry fruit\, cinnamon\, clove\, and full Oakville structure.\n- Groth Cabernet Sauvignon 2022 - A streamlined\, silky Oakville Cabernet built on black cherry\, subtle cedar\, Merlot\, Petit Verdot\, and fresh structure.\n- Groth Oakville Estate Sauvignon Blanc 2023 - Crisp and clean\, showing peach\, tangerine\, lemon curd\, wet stone\, white pepper\, and bright citrus lift.\nExperience the range of Groth's Oakville estate wines\, from bright Sauvignon Blanc to age-worthy Cabernet.
LOCATION:4201 W Fourth St Reno\, NV 89523
SUMMARY:Flights & Flatbread with Groth
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR